erican Nations Fail brings together leading Latin Americanists from several disciplines to address the topic of how and why contemporary development strategies have failed to curb rampant poverty and underdevelopment throughout the region. Given the dramatic political turns in contemporary Latin America, this book offers a much-needed explanation and analysis of the factors that are key to making sense of development today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic developmentzLatin AmericaxHistory. 0aSustainable developmentzLatin America. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh1 aAbeles, Martín, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAguiar de Medeiros, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntonio Ocampo, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaldentey, Esteban Pérez, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCenteno, Miguel A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerraro, Agustín E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallagher, Kevin P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarry, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreno-Brid, Juan Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNava, Jean C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPortes, Alejandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPérez Caldentey, Esteban, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRay, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValdecantos, Sebastián, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVernengo